document_title: Right testicular pain: Causes, symptoms and prevention
subsection_content: Right testicular pain is a pain that occurs only in the right testicle and has absolutely no symptoms on the opposite side. This phenomenon is not common but can be a warning sign of some serious medical problems that need to be monitored and treated early.
